<td valign="top" bgcolor="white">
<font color="black" face="Arial,Sans-serif" size="2"><big><b>

Get the tips you need about Windows Vista

</b><br></big>

The all-new <i>Windows Vista Secrets</i> helps novices 
and experts alike understand Microsoft's latest operating system. 
"To really appreciate what is in Vista, you almost 
need to read through the leading book on the product, <i>Windows Vista 
Secrets,</i> by Brian Livingston and Paul Thurrott," writes Rob Enderle, 
principal analyst of the Enderle Group, in TechNewsWorld. "It's 595 
pages of things you can do with this product &#8212; most of which 
you probably wouldn't have discovered for some time, let alone right 
at first." Check the book out now for tips you can use.<br>

<b>More information:</b>
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/2c451fh/?url=www.amazon.com%2Fexec%2Fobidos%2FASIN%2F0764577042%2Fref%3Dnosim%2Fisbnat"><u>United&nbsp;States</u></a>&nbsp;/ 
