<a name="wacky"></a>
<hr>
<font color="#666666" face="Verdana, Arial, Sans-serif" size="1">WACKY WEB WEEK<br><br></font>


<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="black" size="4"><b>Practice your 
bunny-surgery skills online</b><br></font>
<font face="Arial,Sans-Serif" color="black" size="1"><br></font>


<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="white" summary="Wacky Web Week">
<tr>
<td width="110" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">
<a href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/74f066h/?url=www.10mg.nl%2F">
<img src="http://WindowsSecrets.com/images/wsn/W070517bunnysmall.jpg"
align="left" width="110" height="100" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="3"
title="image" alt="image"></a>
</td>

<td width="510" align="left" valign="top" bgcolor="FFFFFF">

<font face="Arial,Sans-serif" color="#000000" size="2">
If you've ever wanted be a surgeon, you've probably realized that your first 
attempts should be on something safe &#8212; for example, on a stuffed bunny. 
Now, you can do just that, without ever hurting the bunny!<br><br>

This Flash-based game is a demonstration of the services offered by 10mg 
Interactive of Amsterdam. It lets you resuscitate a dead bunny, then shave 
and operate, saving its life &#8212; if you can. But, you may find surgery 
is harder than you thought. Even virtual surgery!<br>
<a name="ws_wacky web week" href="http://WindowsSecrets.com/links/p3472n61w1axd/74f066h/?url=www.10mg.nl%2F">Play the game</a><br></font>

